Closest I've got is this little story copy-pasted from the description of pic related.

It was just another trip into the ruins to scavenge machine parts. The cities had been vacated in such a sudden panic all those years ago that not even the thousands of cars within had escaped. Now the communities in the countryside needed their transmissions, motors, and suspensions.

You'd been a mechanic before The Arrival, and your skills had helped you survive the chaos of the alien invasion and their monstrous armies. Things seemed hopeless before humanity managed to repel the immense invasion ships that had darkened Earth's skies.

The masterminds of the invasion had been repelled, but their armies remained, suddenly freed from their enthrallment. Their single minded destruction of mankind overnight dissipated, replaced with mere curiosity and idleness. The cities they had been engineered to obliterate became their haunts, where they lounged about, only really rousing to inspect anything that came close or to fight with one another over territory. They didn't seem to eat, living by bioengineered fusion within their immense, powerful bodies, they now seemed to be content to toy with whatever of humanity they had at hand.

Most of humanity was forbidden from entering these cities, as the kaiju were dangerous even though they no longer held any hatred for our species. You however were one of the few who had been granted permission to scavenge there when you proved to be fortunate -or unfortunate- enough to earn the 'continued attention' of a kaiju within the ruins.

The pavement leapt beneath your feet as the kaiju sat down suddenly, crushing the street down onto the sewers and subways beneath. She remained focused on you as she hefted a train car effortlessly in one hand. With an effortless gesture, like someone might unwrap a candy bar, she twisted the side off and pulled something from it, slowly setting it before you in the valley she had made between her legs.
